I think this is actually doable, only I'd rather block the player when
he's attempting to perform forbidden actions, rather than kill him.
You know, the old cheezy &quot;A mysterious force stops you&quot;.

Now, you can have the area that will be explored by the &quot;past self&quot;
marked in the game, and &quot;out of limits&quot; for the &quot;future self&quot;. As
the &quot;past self&quot; explores, this area will shrink, allowing the &quot;future
self&quot; access. The &quot;future self&quot; might be blocked when trying to enter
this area, or he might become somehow ephemeral and invisible to the &quot;past
self&quot; -- or he might even be just hiding on purpose to avoid the meeting.
Of course, he would refuse dropping any items. An interesting use would be
to &quot;ride&quot; at the edge of the &quot;past self&quot; perception, so that you can avoid
fighting, and stay back once in a while to become physical and collect
items.

I just had another idea, a little ironic, though. The &quot;future self&quot; is
allowed to do anything, but as soon as any of the &quot;replayed&quot; moves of
the &quot;past self&quot; becomes invalid, he becomes aware of his presence, and,
naturally attacks his &quot;future self&quot;, always fighting to death. No matter
which side wins, it's game over.

