OK, I've been thinking about a good plot that could make such a game
interesting and I've come up with this:

THE LAST DAY

The evil wizard Moloch's plan for world domination is nearly
completed. Tonight, when the solar eclipse gets to its climax, the
last of the Seven Rituals of Koth will be completed, and a Gate to the
Plane of Darkness will be opened. Once the Gate is opened, there is no
way to close it again, so the world will be swarmed with evil
creatures and all sentient races will be enslaved.

Many brave heroes have tried to stop Moloch's plans, but none of them
has returned. Seeing that the world was running out of time to stop
the evil plot, Ellnod the Sage has worked long hours during the last
days to complete his last invention: the Temporal Anchor. This
powerful artifact allows you to set an anchor in time to which you can
return as many times as you wish.

You are the last chance for saving your world. Inexperienced as you
are, you're the last fighter left in the village of Zondra (near
Moloch's lair) after all the others have disappeared into the evil
wizard's dungeon. The elder Ellnod hands you the Anchor, sets an
anchoring point at that same moment and instructs you on what you must
do: you must try to find Moloch and stop him, but as one day will
surely not be enough, you must use the Anchor before the time of the
eclipse, so as to return one day back and have another day to find the
evil wizard. However, you should not abuse the Anchor, since each time
you use it will make your quest slightly harder, for you will have to
avoid all the past incarnations of yourself: if you interact with any
of them, you will spawn a paradox that will destroy you, and probably
the world as well.
