Why not just create parallel universes?

As you play, the events in the world are recorded. When you go back in
time, these events are replayed until you interact with something that
makes the events invalid. After that, things are just controlled by
the AI, including your past self. Events still get recorded when you
travel back in time, including the actions future-you takes in the
past.

So, killing your grandfather means that when you go back to the
present will take you to a universe where you never existed, where
supposedly the game would have simulated accordingly.

Of course, if time travel is unlimited then this allows situations
like going back to the start over and over again until you've amassed
an army of yourself. Whether this is a feature or a bug is up to the
developer.

As an aside, I've always wondered what a Dr. Who RL would be like.
