I did realize a flaw in my previous message; it depends on how well
you can simulate your world.

If it's just a single dungeon and you go only a few hours back in
time, just simulating monster and past-self actions should be enough.
If you're creating a whole world and the player can travel hundreds of
years or more, you'll have to simulate family trees, wars, weather and
crops, ... The list just starts to inflate.

You also need a good way of recording every performed action, pending
action, and AI goal to be able to play them back when the player
travels back in time.
