I was playing World of Warcraft this last few days, and I got to the
bit where you travel back in time to Durnholde Keep (AKA Old Hillsbrad
Foothills).  The instance is hectic, but in spare times - or after
completing - you can visit a town called Southshore that still exists
some years later in (your) history.  You see characters you have fought
with, or against, or otherwise interacted with - in instances that were
recent in your timeline, but are still in their future.

You see some little kids playing, Sally Whitemane and Renault Mograine
(and their friend Vishnu who grows up to be the torturer).  They have a
mock fight with a frog, and reprise the battle where you (in your
timeline) have already killed them (a long time ago - thirty levels or
so) in the Scarlet Cathedral.  But for them the Cathedral event must
have been the reprise; they remember that little battle they had as
kids, and say the same words.  I found that rather affecting.

